&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a2&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;I will let rain a rain of weapons on the earth, and with a flood of weapons I will fill the cardinal directions.  (cf [[Couvreur 1964]]: 246; [[Schmidt KT 2001]]: 325)&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;670&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;a5&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;There is no one in this world who could have brought me into this misfortune by [his] power.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;340&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b3, B 94 a4&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;For now I will perish with the root.  (cf [[Schmidt KT 2001]]: 326)&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;295&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Translations from [[Schmidt KT 1974]]
&lt;table class="table_lines"&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Lines&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Translation&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th&gt;Pages&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;b1&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;span title="The arrows of a vengeful(?) one have struck (my heart) violently."&gt;Die Pfeile eines Rachsüchtigen(?) haben mich heftig (ins Herz) getroffen.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;368&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MM: am Anfang ergänzt Du (a)ktajñei, aber in der Parallele steh auch THT 94 a 2 steht es auch ohne a. Offenbar wollest Du da einen Kommentar zu Schmidt schreiben? Kann es nicht tatsächlich "grateful" bedeuten? So übersetzt jedenfall Georges in PK NS 36 and 20, obwohl es da ja nicht bezeugt ist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]]: 213 translates: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 I shall be ... on this earth &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 Indra ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a4 [He] says: 'O great king!' &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a5 [to remember]. Thereupon he says: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a6 What power could hinder me? O compassionate one! &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b1 The arrows of ingratitude struck me violently &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 I shall see this miserable [and wretched] world. The Buddha ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b3 And yet I [shall ...] with the root &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 [Those] without hair [shall] ... &lt;/p&gt;</item>
               <item n="ms_old">IOL Toch 69</item>
               <item n="m_remarks_old">&lt;p&gt;According to [[Broomhead I]]: 213 "[w]ritten in medium ductus, and very clearly preserved, it is the left edge of a six line manuscript. A number in the margin verso is not completely clear and may be either '41' or '71'".
He also identifies this fragment as folios 21-22 (op.cit.).&lt;/p&gt;</item>
